comments.body:
The pattern:

```cpp
SetMockTime(Now<NodeSeconds>());
SetMockTime(Now<NodeSeconds>() - 1h);
SetMockTime(Now<NodeSeconds>() + 1h);
```
while unlikely makes it possible something unexpected to happen if 1h passes in between (ðŸ‘€). Would be more robust to assign to a variable, whose value will not change during the test:
```cpp
const auto start = Now<NodeSeconds>();
SetMockTime(start);
SetMockTime(start - 1h);
SetMockTime(start + 1h);
```

